This download contains the following series on the Power of God by Watermark Church.  

1 Power of Grace:
We acknowledge our complete dependence on the goodness and grace of God. We have benefited from the kind intention of His will; therefore, we eagerly extend it to others. &quot;For by grace you have been saved through faith. And this is not your own doing; it is the gift of God, not a result of works, so that no one may boast.&quot; Ephesians 2:8-9 (ESV)

2 Power of Prayer:
Prayer is an invitation for us to participate in the incredible things God is doing. Colossians 4:2 calls us to &quot;Continue steadfastly in prayer, being watchful in it with thanksgiving.&quot; Colossians 4:2 (ESV) Communication defines our relationships, we are encouraged to continually be diligent in prayer.

3 Power of Love:
The world will know us as Christ's disciples by our legitimate love for people and our dedication to assess the real need. We believe that lost people matter to God; therefore, they matter to us. It is through this authenticity that we share Christ's love for people. &quot;For the Son of Man came to seek and to save the lost.&quot; Luke 19:10

4 Power of The Gospel:
God is about seeking lost and broken people. The image and purpose of Jesus's ministry is to rescue those who are lost. He seeks to save because He loves the lost and desires a relationship with us. &quot;For the Son of Man came to seek and to save the lost.&quot; Luke 19:10 (ESV)


